#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Following ancient signs, Gwiti and Arkal-Thil arrive at a cramped, shadowed "
"cave passage. Even their dark vision is limited by the oppressive gloom "
"surrounding them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:114
msgid ""
"So, we’re finally here... the resting place of Crelanu’s tome, hidden beyond "
"these darkness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:118
msgid ""
"It feels different, master — colder, and something... alive? This place "
"seems to push back against us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:122
msgid ""
"The book is well hidden, indeed. But that only proves its worth. We will "
"claim it, and this place will tremble at our presence."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:141
msgid ""
"<i>At the far end of the cave, a massive stone wall marked with ancient "
"runes blocks the way forward. The runes pulse faintly, their magical seals "
"still strong after centuries.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:146
msgid ""
"Master, these runes seem to hold a protective spell. We may need to break it "
"piece by piece."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:150
msgid ""
"Then we must locate the guardians — no doubt they will appear the moment we "
"set foot on these sigils."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Nagou
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:163
msgid "Nagou"
msgstr "Nagou"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:170
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:352
msgid "Defeat all enemy units"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:204
msgid "You shall not... enter the sacred sanctum..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:208
msgid ""
"How amusing. Even in death, they cling to hollow oaths. Arkal-Thil, another "
"seal falls."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:241
msgid ""
"<i>With the last guardian vanquished, the runes on the wall fade. The "
"barrier crumbles, revealing a hidden chamber beyond — at its center, "
"surrounded by shallow pools, rests the Book of Crelanu upon a pedestal.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:285
msgid ""
"<i>As Gwiti seizes the tome, tremors shake the cave, and shadows creep from "
"the depths. Feral creatures, bound to the tome’s defense, slink from the "
"pools and shadows.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:311
msgid "Master, the guardians of the cave awaken!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:315
msgid ""
"They are no more than shadows bound by ancient spells. We’ll crush them as "
"we did the keepers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:387
msgid ""
"With the final guardian defeated, a deathly silence settles once more. The "
"tome, now Gwiti’s, pulses with dark power."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gwiti Ha'atel
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:392
msgid ""
"With Crelanu’s knowledge, Wesnoth will witness my wrath. Let us leave this "
"forsaken cave, Arkal-Thil."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arkal-Thil
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Book_of_Crelanu.cfg:396
msgid ""
"Yes, master. May all who defy you be swallowed by the shadows we leave "
"behind."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:7
msgid ""
"Five years prior... the autumn of the fourth year of King Delvhar I’s reign."
msgstr "5 年前...... Delvhar I 世の治世 4 年目の秋。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:10
msgid ""
"The northern lands were undergoing a gradual transformation. From among the "
"divided tribes a great chief arose to unite them under a single banner and "
"lead the orcs out of the stagnation that had lasted since the death of "
"Kapou’e, the Son of the Black-Eye."
msgstr ""
"北方の地には、徐々に変化の波が押し寄せていた。争いの絶えないオークの氏族達の"
"中から、一人の偉大な族長が現れ、戦う部族達を一つの旗印の下に統一する事に成功"
"したのである。この力は、オーク諸族を長き眠りから覚醒させるには十分であった "
"—— それは、黒眼の子 Kapou’e の死以来続いていた停滞からの目覚めであった。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:13
msgid ""
"Yet the orcs remained true to their nature, pursuing twin ambitions: plunder "
"and conquest."
msgstr ""
"しかしそれでも、オーク達は己が本性に従い、略奪と征服という二つの野望を追い求"
"めた。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:17
msgid ""
"They began systematically raiding elven and human settlements and outposts. "
"What struck terror in the hearts of the people was not the familiar pattern "
"of scattered raids, but rather the unprecedented scale of these assaults — "
"massive battles waged by armies of emboldened orcs."
msgstr ""
"オーク達は、エルフと人間の集落や前哨地を組織的に襲撃し始めた。人々の心に恐怖"
"を植え付けたのは、見慣れた散発的な襲撃ではない。それは、大胆さを増したオーク"
"の軍勢による大規模な襲撃という、かつてない規模の侵攻であった。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This tide of warfare now surged toward the northern stronghold of the Stone "
"of Erzen."
msgstr "この戦いの波は今や、Erzen の石と呼ばれる北方の要塞へと押し寄せていた。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Yet the massive orcish reinforcements that arrived later utterly decimated "
"the Wesnothian forces. The battlefield of Erzen ran red with blood."
msgstr ""
"後に到着した大規模なオークの増援軍は、Wesnoth の軍勢を完全に蹂躙した。Erzen "
"の戦場は血に染まった。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Consumed by fury, Blucyn hunted Gwiti and Nati with murderous intent. "
"Without their dark interference, he believed, there would have been no "
"chaos, no defeat on that fateful field. At last, the brothers were captured."
msgstr ""
"怒りに駆られた Blucyn は、殺意を胸に秘めて Gwiti と Nati を追い詰めた。彼らの"
"邪な干渉がなければ、あの運命の戦場での混沌も敗北もなかったはずだと信じていた"
"のだ。そして遂に、兄弟は捕らえられた。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:36
msgid ""
"The Ha’atel brothers were bound in iron chains and cast aboard a rudderless "
"ship. They were condemned to drown in the endless ocean, for the Wesnothians "
"feared their corpses might rise again from any earthly grave..."
msgstr ""
"Ha’atel 兄弟は鉄の鎖で縛られ、舵を失った船に投じられた。Wesnoth の民は、彼ら"
"の死体が地上の墓から蘇ることを恐れ、果てしない大海での溺死を宣告したのであ"
"る......"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:40
msgid "<i>...but fate had other designs.</i>"
msgstr "........だが、運命は異なる策を秘めていた。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:48
msgid ""
"Heeding the enigmatic guidance of a distant voice, Gwiti Ha’atel pressed "
"forward through unfamiliar terrain, drawn inexorably toward a confrontation "
"that seemed to have been orchestrated long before his arrival."
msgstr ""
"遠くからの謎めいた声の導きに従い、Gwiti Ha’atel は見知らぬ土地を進んだ。彼の"
"到来より遥か以前から仕組まれていた対峙へと、否応なく引き寄せられるが如く。"

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:56
msgid ""
"Once more, the voice of the master resonated in Gwiti’s mind, urging him "
"forward into the depths of his dark destiny."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:59
msgid ""
"<i>“Gwiti, do not be hasty in seeking your vengeance against Wesnoth. The "
"path you tread is fraught with peril, and your ultimate aim requires the "
"Skull of Morgorath. The whispers of the world’s sacrifices beckon you to "
"heed their call.”</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:63
msgid ""
"<i>“Journey forth to the forbidding mountains in the northwest. There, amid "
"the ancient stones, a power awaits that will elevate you beyond your wildest "
"dreams. Embrace this calling, for it shall bestow upon you the strength to "
"shape your fate.”</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:72
msgid ""
"As Gwiti regained his senses, the skies overhead darkened, a thick blanket "
"of clouds rolling in as if in response to his mounting fury. He found "
"himself once again on the desolate battlefield, but this time, the voice "
"that had lured him this far was silent, its influence faded."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:75
msgid ""
"Frustrated and drained from his failed quest, Gwiti looked at the half of "
"the skull in his hand, feeling the weight of wasted time. Half a relic was "
"no path to ultimate power. Still seething, he recalled an artifact from his "
"memory — the Book of Crelanu, a tome of legendary might that had long been "
"sealed away. His resolve hardened; if he could not wield the full Skull, he "
"would claim Crelanu’s tome, bending its power to his own dark designs."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:84
msgid ""
"According to the journal Gwiti uncovered, following the death of Delfador "
"the Great, a custom emerged: the Book of Crelanu would be entrusted only to "
"one of the King’s closest advisors."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:87
msgid ""
"However, this decision proved a grave miscalculation. The tome eventually "
"fell into the hands of Mal-Ravanal, unleashing the deadliest undead "
"incursion Wesnoth had ever faced, nearly bringing the kingdom to ruin."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:90
msgid ""
"In the aftermath, no mage dared claim stewardship of Crelanu’s tome. "
"Instead, the mages resolved to conceal it in a place no mortal would easily "
"reach, while rumors spread that it lay protected within the Tower of Kaleon."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:93
msgid ""
"Now, five centuries later, Gwiti has retraced their steps, descending to the "
"deepest reaches of the underground labyrinth, ever closer to the elusive "
"tome..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:102
msgid ""
"Concerned about the presence of undead legions within Wesnoth, the king "
"ordered lords across the land to remain vigilant. In the midst of these "
"precautions, one of the elves who had survived the attack on Kaleon’s Tower "
"delivered urgent news to the council Ka’lian."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: The_Shadow_Returns/episode1/storytxt.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Recognizing the gravity of the situation, Lord Caraldur himself led an elven "
"battalion toward the region. Meanwhile, Lord Aretu of Wesnoth and General "
"Leonard mobilized their own forces, converging on the path of Gwiti, as "
"their pursuit brought them all to a single, decisive location."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Demonic Lich, race=undead
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/demons/Demonic_Lich.cfg:4
msgid "Demonic Lich"
msgstr "悪魔のリッチ"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demonic Lich, race=undead
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/demons/Demonic_Lich.cfg:25
msgid ""
"In the darkest depths of the void stands Morgorath, a being whose very "
"essence defies the natural order. Once a demon prince of terrible power, he "
"chose to embrace undeath, fusing infernal might with necromantic mastery. "
"The result is an abomination that commands both hellfire and death itself — "
"a lich whose very presence corrupts the boundary between the mortal realm "
"and the infernal abyss."
msgstr ""
"虚無の最も暗き深淵に、その本質さえも自然の摂理に反する存在、Morgorath が立っ"
"ている。かつて凄まじい力を持つ魔王であった彼は、不死を受け入れることを選び、"
"地獄の力と死霊術の極意を融合させた。その結果生まれたのは、地獄の業火と死その"
"ものを支配する忌まわしき存在 —— その存在自体が死すべき者の世界と地獄の深淵と"
"の境界を蝕む死霊である。"

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/demons/Demonic_Lich.cfg:43
msgid "infernal chill"
msgstr "地獄の冷風"

#. [unit_type]: id=Sylvan Warden, race=elf, gender=female
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/elves/Sylvan_Warden.cfg:4
msgid "female^Sylvan Warden"
msgstr "森の番人"

#. [unit_type]: id=Sylvan Warden, race=elf, gender=female
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/elves/Sylvan_Warden.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Though gifted in the ancient arts, Elynia’s mastery remains unfinished — a "
"journey cut tragically short when darkness claimed her mentor’s life. The "
"sacred magic flows strong within her, yet each spell carries the bitter "
"weight of that loss. Her ethereal beauty masks a heart tempered by battle "
"and grief, her eyes reflecting not merely power, but an unwavering resolve "
"born from witnessing the price of failure. Now she stands as guardian of "
"these lands, though she knows not the true scope of the realm she must "
"protect."
msgstr ""
"古の術に才能こそ持ち合わせているものの、Elynia の熟達は未だ道半ばである —— 闇"
"が彼女の師の命を奪った時、その道のりは悲劇的に断ち切られたのだ。聖なる魔法は"
"彼女の内に強く流れているが、その一つ一つの呪文には、喪失の苦い重みが宿ってい"
"る。彼女の幽玄な美しさは、戦いと悲しみに鍛えられた心を覆い隠し、その瞳は単な"
"る力だけでなく、失敗の代償を目の当たりにして生まれた揺るぎない決意を映し出し"
"ている。今や彼女はこれらの地の守護者として立っているが、自らが守るべき領域の"
"真の広がりを知る時はまだ先である。"

#. [unit_type]: id=Deathmaster, race=human
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Deathmaster.cfg:4
msgid "Deathmaster"
msgstr "死人使い"

#. [unit_type]: id=Deathmaster, race=human
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Deathmaster.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Through his descent into darkness, Ha’atel has attained powers forbidden to "
"mortal kind, yet at a terrible cost: the undead to whom he pledged his soul "
"now steadily claim his mortal form. As time’s dark tide flows ever onward, "
"he inches closer to becoming that which he commands — a true being of "
"undeath, an abomination to all that draw breath."
msgstr ""
"暗黒への堕落を通じて、Ha’atel は死すべき者には禁じられた力を手に入れた。しか"
"しそれには恐ろしい代償が伴っていた。彼が魂を捧げた不死者たちが、今や着実に彼"
"の肉体を蝕んでいるのだ。暗き時の潮が絶え間なく流れる中、彼は自らが支配する者 "
"——不死の真なる存在、息あるモノ全てにとっての忌まわしき存在—— へと着実に前進す"
"るだろう。"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demilich, race=undead
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Demilich.cfg:4
msgid "Demilich"
msgstr "デミリッチ"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demilich, race=undead
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Demilich.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The transformation has taken its toll, as Ha’atel’s form now exists between "
"life and death. His flesh grows ever colder while his powers reach "
"horrifying new heights. With each ritual performed, the boundary between "
"master and servant blurs further, as the whispers of the dead guide his "
"hand. Those who witness his passing speak only of shadows that writhe with "
"unnatural life, and of darkness that pulses with its own heartbeat."
msgstr ""
"変容は確実に進行し、Ha’atel の姿は今や生と死の狭間に存在している。彼の肉体は"
"次第に冷たさを増し、その力は戦慄すべき新たな高みへと達している。儀式を重ねる"
"毎に、主と従者の境界は一層曖昧になり、死者たちの囁きが彼の手を導く。彼の通過"
"を目撃した者たちは、不自然な生命を持つ蠢く影と、独自の鼓動を打つ闇についての"
"み語るのである。"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dread Lich, race=undead
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Dread_Lich.cfg:4
msgid "Dread Lich"
msgstr "恐怖のリッチ"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dread Lich, race=undead
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Dread_Lich.cfg:25
msgid ""
"At the culmination of his shadowed pilgrimage, Ha’atel made the ultimate "
"sacrifice to the darkness that had long embraced him, crossing the threshold "
"into immortality itself. At the zenith of his power, he transcended his "
"mortal coil to become a lich — the very embodiment of mortal terror "
"awakened. In this transformation, he crossed a boundary from which there "
"could be no return. Perhaps the cold comfort of immortality and boundless "
"power serves as solace for all he has surrendered in its pursuit."
msgstr ""
"影なす巡礼の極みにおいて、Ha’atel は長きに渡って己を包み込んだ闇への最後の犠"
"牲を捧げ、不死性という領域へと足を踏み入れた。その力の頂点において、彼は死す"
"べき肉体を超越し、リッチ ——人の恐怖の具現化—— となった。この変容において、彼"
"は二度と戻ることのできぬ境界を越えたのだ。そして、不死と無限の力という冷たき"
"慰めは、その追求の中で失った全てに対する慰藉となるだろう。"

#. [unit_type]: id=Initiate, race=human
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Initiate.cfg:4
msgid "Initiate"
msgstr "下級術師"

#. [unit_type]: id=Initiate, race=human
#: The_Shadow_Returns/units/undead/Initiate.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Young Ha’atel’s essence is so deeply intertwined with death magic that he "
"has forsaken even the most basic forms of combat. Instead, he nurtures the "
"dark powers that bloom within his very being. What truly instills terror is "
"his unwavering devotion to the pursuit of power — a hunger that knows no "
"bounds."
msgstr ""
"若き Ha’atel の魂は死の魔法と深く結び付いており、最も基本的な戦闘の形さえも放"
"棄している。その代わりに、彼は己の存在の内に芽吹く暗黒の力を育んでいる。真に"
"恐怖を呼び起こすのは、力を追い求める彼の揺るぎない献身 —— 際限を知らぬ渇望で"
"ある。"

